          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "You were the only child of wealthy socialites, an acessory to your parents' lives just as much as your father's Rolex or your mother's purse chihuahua. Encouraged to 'follow your bliss,' you followed it straight to art school, where you had dreams of writing the next Rent or Cats. You even had a patron, a mysterious beautiful woman who would come to at night and serve as your muse. You thought yours was a love for the ages - and it was, just not the way you thought. She brought you over into her world of blood and darkness. And you might have stood a chance, except for the absolute shit life that is a Camarilla neonoate. You couldn't hack it. You were too used to privilege, to getting your way, to have your thoughts listened to and your feelings matter. You kept acting out, to the point where your sire was almost forced to kill you. Almost. Instead, she abjured you, and sent you away. You found the Sabbat, and though you still had to work your way up from the bottom, you managed that in a space of five years, not the fifty or more the Camarilla promised you. And while your pack listens to you, you want to get back to a place where *everyone* listens to you. And you've latched onto the Pander movement as your way out. \n\nDark Secret: You tell everyone that you are Pander, but you're not, not technically. You know exactly what bloodline you are, and you just can't bring yourself to divest yourself of your Blood with Pander's ritae. Whenever anyone asks, you tell them about being rejected by your sire and finding acceptance in the freedom of the Sabbat, and the rounds of Praise Caine which result usually distract them. But it would be embarassing if your secret ever did come out."
        ],
